<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Thunberg</emphasis>
s.n. (holotype BM000930466! ex Herb. Roemer; isotype UPS).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
Perennial herb, thinly pubescent in all vegetative parts; rootstock thin, woody; stems to 70 cm, prostrate. Leaves petiolate, relatively small, lanceolate to ovate in outline, the central lobe 1- 5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.8, cm, oblong to lanceolate, dentate, pinnatisect to pinnatifid, characteristically cordate-deltoid, auricles prominent, usually bifurcate, 0.3-1.5 cm, usually dentate, apex acute or obtuse; petioles 3-12 mm. Flowers solitary (rarely paired), axillary, pedunculate, peduncles 0.8-3 cm; bracteoles 3-7 mm, subulate to linear; pedicels 3-12 mm; outer sepals 9-12 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-6 mm, ovate, acute to acuminate, inner sepals scarioius, pubescent only in central vertical lines; corolla 1.6-2.8 cm, white or pink, very shallowly lobed, the midpetaline bands pubescent, terminating in a tooth; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided c. 7 mm above base; stigmas 4 mm, linear. Capsule glabrous; seeds smooth. [
<bibRefCitation author="Meeuse, ADL" journalOrPublisher="Bothalia" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="641 - 792" refId="B225" refString="Meeuse, ADL, 1958 1957. The South African Convolvulaceae. Bothalia 6: 641 - 792" title="The South African Convolvulaceae." volume="6" year="1958">Meeuse 1958</bibRefCitation>
: 690; 
<bibRefCitation author="Meeuse, ADL" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Southern Africa" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 138" refId="B226" refString="Meeuse, ADL, Welman, WG, 2000. Convolvulaceae. Flora of Southern Africa volume 28 (part 1): 1 - 138" title="Convolvulaceae." volume="volume 28" year="2000">Meeuse and Welman 2000</bibRefCitation>
: 47 (map and plate)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
South Africa: Eastern Cape, KwaZulu-Natal, Free State, North West, Gauteng, Mpumalanga, Limpopo (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Moss</emphasis>
7122, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Bolus</emphasis>
6847, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Cooper</emphasis>
790, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Meeuse</emphasis>
9376, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Schlechter</emphasis>
3479); Lesotho (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Dieterlen</emphasis>
387).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
Distinguished by its essentially pinnately-nerved central leaf lobe. It seems close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernh. ex Krauss, Flora 27 (2): 829. 1844. (Krauss" authorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus natalensis" order="Solanales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Convolvulus natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
particularly as represented by 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Hoggarth in Wood</emphasis>
4179, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Dietelen</emphasis>
38751, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Galpin</emphasis>
430 &amp; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Williams</emphasis>
154, which 
<bibRefCitation author="Meeuse, ADL" journalOrPublisher="Bothalia" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="641 - 792" refId="B225" refString="Meeuse, ADL, 1958 1957. The South African Convolvulaceae. Bothalia 6: 641 - 792" title="The South African Convolvulaceae." volume="6" year="1958">Meeuse (1958</bibRefCitation>
: 689) treated as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. var. var. transvaalensis" order="Solanales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="natalensis" subSpecies="var." variety="transvaalensis">var. transvaalensis</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernh. ex Krauss, Flora 27 (2): 829. 1844. (Krauss" authorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus natalensis" order="Solanales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Convolvulus natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is also close to some forms of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus austrafricanus" order="Solanales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austrafricanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Convolvulus austrafricanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differing in little more than the larger flowers. It has been much confused historically being also treated as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burm. f., Fl. Ind. (N. L. Burman) Prodr. Fl. Cap. 5. 1768. (Burman" authorityYear="1768" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus capensis" order="Solanales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Convolvulus capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, JG" journalOrPublisher="Lovell, Reeve &amp; Co, London" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" pagination="45 - 87" refId="B20" refString="Baker, JG, Wright, CH, 1904. Flora Capensis volume 4: Hydrophyllaceae to Pedalineae. Lovell, Reeve &amp; Co, London: 45 - 87" title="Flora Capensis volume 4: Hydrophyllaceae to Pedalineae" year="1904">Baker and Wright 1904</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
